    "Id": "chassisdef_dominatrix_DTX-96",
    "Name": "Dominatrix",
    "Details": "The DTX-96 is a unique Solaris VII gladiatorial machine commissioned by Canopian noblewoman Anya Sokolov. MASC pushes the 55-ton frame to 129 kph in short bursts, closing distance before opponents can react. A Chain Whip and Vibroblade handle melee while Spikes punish anything that strikes back. Twin Medium VSP Lasers and a Small VSP Laser reward the close range the design constantly demands, and a hidden Flamer in the center torso adds one final unpleasant surprise.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Melee Actuators</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.05</color></b>",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_dominatrix"
  },
  "VariantName": "DTX-96",
  "ChassisTags": {
    "items": [],
    "tagSetSourceFile": ""
  },
  "StockRole": "Close Assault",
  "YangsThoughts": "A Canopian noblewoman got bored and commissioned a gladiatorial mech on Solaris VII. That is the whole story. Anya Sokolov wanted something fast, close-range and built around melee, and whoever built this delivered exactly that. The VSP lasers get more accurate the closer you are, the MASC gets you there faster than anyone expects, and then the whip and vibroblade do the rest. She won several tournaments with it. Looking at the loadout, that does not surprise me at all.",
